begin model

#@title: p53/Mdm2 and NHEJ DNA-repair with p53/p21 senescence signaling (Dolan et al., 2015)

#@description: |
#  Integrated single-cell STOCHASTIC model that couples non-homologous
#  end-joining (NHEJ) repair of DNA double-strand breaks (DSBs) to
#  ATM/p53/Mdm2 damage signaling and p53/p21-mediated early senescence in
#  human fibroblasts. Fifty independent genomic loci (DNA1..DNA50) each carry
#  a break-state site (ok/sdsb/cdsb) and a histone H2AX component
#  (u/p/foc). Background reactive oxygen species (ROS), produced at a
#  constant rate and degraded first-order (steady state ~kROS/kdROS = 10
#  molecules), convert intact loci into simple or complex DSBs. A DSB
#  recruits Ku70/80 then DNA-PKcs (fast D-NHEJ) or PARP-1 then Ligase III
#  (slow backup B-NHEJ); Ku is redox-inactivated by ROS. Each DSB also
#  activates ATM (an ATM molecule is switched from state 0 to the locus
#  index i=1..50, tagging the site), which phosphorylates H2AX to build a
#  damage focus and phosphorylates p53. Phosphorylated p53 escapes Mdm2-
#  targeted degradation, driving pulses of p53 that raise Mdm2, p21 and
#  GADD45; p21 feeds back through p38 to raise ROS, and (when p21 stays high)
#  flips a Sen switch that depletes Ku70/80 and PARP-1.
#
#  As deposited here IRRADIATION IS OFF (the acute IR event and its timer
#  functions are commented out), so damage is driven only by chronic
#  background ROS: this is the non-irradiated baseline (Fig. 4 in Dolan et
#  al., 2015). Simulated network-free with NFsim, single cells show near-
#  constant ROS (~10), occasional transient DSBs/foci, low basal p53/p21 with
#  damage-triggered p53 pulses, and no progression to senescence.

#@keyword: |
#  DNA damage repair, non-homologous end joining, NHEJ, double-strand break,
#  p53, MDM2, p21, ATM, H2AX, gamma-H2AX foci, Ku70/80, DNA-PKcs, PARP-1,
#  Ligase IV, Ligase III, reactive oxygen species, cellular senescence,
#  p38, GADD45, stochastic, network-free simulation, NFsim, rule-based model,
#  negative feedback, Homo sapiens

#@reference: |
#  Dolan DWP, Zupanic A, Nelson G, Hall P, Miwa S, Kirkwood TBL, Shanley DP
#  (2015). Integrated Stochastic Model of DNA Damage Repair by Non-homologous
#  End Joining and p53/p21-Mediated Early Senescence Signalling. PLoS Comput
#  Biol 11(5):e1004246. doi:10.1371/journal.pcbi.1004246
#  Model file: Supplementary File S11 (pcbi.1004246.s011.bngl).

#@note: |
#  Model body (molecule types, seed species, observables, functions and the
#  2339 reaction rules) is transcribed VERBATIM from the published SI file
#  pcbi.1004246.s011.bngl; the authors' section comments are preserved. Only
#  house-style wrapping was added: begin model / header metadata, same-line
#  unit comments on parameters (units from S1/S3 Tables) and seed species,
#  'begin species' -> 'begin seed species', and the actions block below.
#  The full reaction network (reported as 4,583 species / 22,341 reactions)
#  is finite but the model is simulated NETWORK-FREE with NFsim: the dynamics
#  of interest are single-cell stochastic trajectories, and if()-gated
#  feedback functions (kku1/kku2/kplus/kminus/kKuDown/kParpDown/kDelete)
#  introduce threshold discontinuities that preclude a meaningful ODE/SSA
#  reproduction of the generated network. The model has no multivalent
#  aggregation or same-complex binding (each locus binds a linear repair
#  chain), so standard/legacy BioNetGen NFsim is a valid reference and no
#  -bscb / -utl flags are needed.
#
#  ONE behavior-preserving re-encoding was required for NFsim >=1.14.3. The
#  published Sen senescence counter used Sen(int~1~10~PLUS~MINUS) with NFsim's
#  PLUS/MINUS increment/decrement operators (int counts 1->10, driven up while
#  p21>15 and down while p21 is low, senescence at int=10). NFsim >=1.14.3
#  rejects PLUS/MINUS when they are declared as allowed states (BNG then exits
#  nonzero), while BNG2.pl requires them declared to parse the rules -- a catch
#  -22 that leaves the operator form unusable here. It is re-encoded as an
#  explicit 10-level integer counter, Sen(int~1~2~..~10), with one increment
#  rule per level at kplus() and one decrement rule per level at kminus() (the
#  Sen_Min guard in kminus still blocks decrementing below 1). This is
#  dynamically identical to the published operator counter and all three
#  engines interpret it the same way. In the deposited (non-irradiated)
#  baseline the counter never leaves int=1 (p21 stays < 15), so
#  Senescent_Counter stays 0 and no cell enters senescence, as reported.
#
#  To enable acute irradiation, uncomment the E()->E()+IR() event, the
#  IR()->Sink() and T()->T()+Time() rules and the Irrad()/IRoff()/Timeoff()
#  functions (see the reaction rules and functions blocks).

#@units_convention: |
#  Natively POPULATION-BASED (molecule counts per cell). First-order rate
#  constants are in /min; second-order rate constants are in /molecule/min
#  (S3 Table '#-1min-1'). NA and V_ref are provided only as a population-
#  conversion basis (counts <-> molar); no volume scaling is applied to the
#  published rate constants.

begin parameters

  # Reserved population-conversion constants (model is natively count-based;
  # provided only so counts can be mapped to molar if ever needed).
  NA     6.02214076e23  # /mol
  V_ref  2.0e-12        # L/cell

  # Rate of p53 mRNA Synthesis
  kp53mRNAsyn  0.06  # /min
  # Rate of p53 mRNA Degradation
  kp53mRNAdeg  0.006  # /min
  # Rate of p53 Synthesis
  kp53syn  0.36  # /min
  # Rate of p53 Degradation
  kp53deg  4.95e-5  # /min
  # Rate of p53 Degradation-MDM2 Dependant
  kp53degMDM2dep  0.0495  # /min
  # Rate of p53 Phosphorylation
  kp53phos  0.36  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of p53 Dephosphorylation
  kp53dphos  30  # /min
  # Rate of MDM2 mRNA Synthesis
  kMDM2mRNAsyn  0.006  # /min
  # Rate of MDM2 mRNA Degradation
  kMDM2mRNAdeg  0.006  # /min
  # Rate of MDM2 Synthesis
  kMDM2syn  0.0297  # /min
  # Rate of MDM2 Degradation
  kMDM2deg  0.02598  # /min
  # Rate of Phosphorylated MDM2 Degradation
  kMDM2pdeg  0.024  # /min
  # Rate of MDM2 Phosphorylation
  kMDM2phos  120  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of p53 Dephosphorylation
  kMDM2dphos  30  # /min
  # Rate of p53 MDM2 Binding
  kp53MDM2bind  0.0693  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of p53 MDM2 Dissociation
  kp53MDM2dis  0.0000693  # /min
  # Rate of p21 mRNA Synthesis (p53)
  kp21mRNAsyn  0.0000036  # /min
  # Rate of p21 mRNA Synthesis (Phosphorylated p53)
  kp21mRNAsynp  0.00036  # /min
  # Rate of p21 mRNA Degradation
  kp21mRNAdeg  0.00144  # /min
  # Rate of p21 Synthesis Step 1
  kp21synstep1  0.024  # /min
  # Rate of p21 Synthesis Step 2
  kp21synstep2  0.0024  # /min
  # Rate of p21 Synthesis Step 3
  kp21synstep3  0.0024  # /min
  # Rate of p21 Degradation
  kp21deg  0.0114  # /min
  # Rate of GADD45 Activation/Production
  kGADD45act  0.00024  # /min
  # Rate of GADD45 Degradation
  kGADD45deg  0.0006  # /min
  # Rate of p38 Phosphorylation
  kp38phos  0.48  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of p38 Dephosphorylation
  kp38dphos  6  # /min
  # Rate of ROS Generation by p38
  kROSgen  1.5  # /min
  kIR  80  # /min
  # Constant rate of ROS production
  kROS  50  # /min
  # ROS degradation rate
  kdROS  5  # /min
  # Rate of simple damage production by ROS
  kdam1  0.000006  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of complex damage production by ROS
  kdam2  0.000006  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of Ku dissociation from a simple break
  kdku1  0.5  # /min
  # Rate of Ku dissociation from a complex break
  kdku2  0.5  # /min
  # Rate of oxidised Ku dissociation from a simple break
  kdku3  5  # /min
  # Rate of oxidised Ku dissociation from a complex break
  kdku4  5  # /min
  # Rate of DNAPK simple break complex formation
  kdnapk1  0.033  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of DNAPK complex break complex formation
  kdnapk2  0.0017  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of DNAPK simple break complex dissociation
  kddnapk1  0.02  # /min
  # Rate of DNAPK complex break complex dissociation
  kddnapk2  0.02  # /min
  # Rate pd DNAPK phosphorylation in a DNAPK complex of a simple break
  kdnapkphos1  0.28  # /min
  # Rate pd DNAPK phosphorylation in a DNAPK complex of a complex break
  kdnapkphos2  0.28  # /min
  # Rate of LigaseIV binding to a simple break complex
  kliIV1  0.00071  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of LigaseIV binding to a complex break complex
  kliIV2  0.00046  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of LigaseIV dissociation from a simple break complex
  kdliIV1  0.0001  # /min
  # Rate of LigaseIV dissociation from a complex break complex
  kdliIV2  0.0001  # /min
  # Rate of DNA repair by LigaseIV of a simple break
  kfixIV1  0.0285  # /min
  # Rate of DNA repair by LigaseIV of a complex break
  kfixIV2  0.0285  # /min
  # Rate of PARP binding to simple break
  kPARP1  0.000077  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of PARP binding to complex break
  kPARP2  0.000065  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of PARP dissociation from a simple break
  kdPARP1  0.02  # /min
  # Rate of PARP dissociation from a complex break
  kdPARP2  0.02  # /min
  # Rate of LigaseIII binding to a simple break
  kliIII1  0.0015  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of LigaseIII binding to a complex break
  kliIII2  0.00024  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of LigaseIII dissociation from a simple break
  kdliIII1  0.0001  # /min
  # Rate of LigaseIII dissociation from a complex break
  kdliIII2  0.0001  # /min
  # Rate of DNA accurate repair by LigaseIII for a simple break
  kfixIII1  0.0006  # /min
  # Rate of DNA accurate repair by LigaseIII for a complex break
  kfixIII2  0.0006  # /min
  # Rate of DNA inaccurate repair by LigaseIII for a simple break
  kfixIII3  0.0009  # /min
  # Rate of dna inaccurate repair by LigaseIII for a complex break
  kfixIII4  0.0009  # /min
  # Rate of ATM Activation
  kATMact  0.0012  # /min
  # Rate of ATM Inactivation
  kATMinact  0.03  # /min
  # Phosphorylation of h2ax via ATM
  kh2axp1  0.1  # /molecule/min
  # Phosphorylation of h2ax via DNA-PKcs
  kh2axp2  0.5  # /min
  # Dephosphorylation of h2ax
  kh2axu  0.01  # /min
  # Creation of damage foci
  kh2axfoc  0.5  # /min
  # Resolution of damage foci
  kfocback  0.03  # /min
  # Creation of complete damage foci
  kh2axfull  0.1  # /molecule/min
  # Resolution of complete damage foci
  kfocfin  0.03  # /min
  # Rate of oxidisation of Ku
  kox  0.000025  # /molecule/min
  # Rate of reduction of Ku
  kred  0.002  # /min
  # Activation of senescent state
  ksen  100  # /min

end parameters

